g.text: Marcus Aurelius Antoninus was a Roman emperor and
Stoic philosopher who reigned from 161 AD to 180 AD.
His greatest surviving work, Meditations, was written
in private and for himself, a kind of self-help journal
with philosophical underpinnings that helped keep
him on his moral path of self-improvement.
